### prompt
Write a function called is_even(number) that takes in one argument (one number as input) and returns True if that number is even. Then execute the line "print is_even(10)" to test if your function works.
### solution
def is_even(number):
  return number % 2 == 0
print is_even(10)
### test
print is_even(3)
print is_even(5)
print is_even(6)
print is_even(2)
print is_even(1)


### hint
The syntax to check and print if one  number is divisible by 3 is
<pre> print 5 % 3 == 0 # this will return False since 5 mod 3 is equal to 2. % just returns the remainder when dividing
</pre>
The syntax to define a function called returnTrue that always returns True is
<pre> def returnTrue():
   return True
</pre>

